      out.write("\n");
      out.write("             <p style=\"color: black;font-size: 1rem;\"><b>1. Course Duration</b>\n");
      out.write("                 : A B.Tech program typically spans 4 years, divided into 8 semesters. Each semester includes core courses, lab sessions, project work, and practical training.\n");
      out.write("               <br><b> 2. Specializations</b>\n");
      out.write("                B.Tech offers various specializations, allowing students to focus on a specific engineering domain. Common branches include:\n");
      out.write("                \n");
      out.write("                Computer Science Engineering (CSE)\n");
      out.write("                Information Technology (IT)\n");
      out.write("                Mechanical Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Civil Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Electrical and Electronics Engineering (EEE)\n");
      out.write("                Electronics and Communication Engineering (ECE)\n");
      out.write("                Chemical Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Aerospace Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Biotechnology\n");
      out.write("                Environmental Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Automobile Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Agricultural Engineering, among others.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>3. Eligibility Requirements</b>\n");
      out.write("                Education: Students must complete 10+2 (higher secondary education) with a focus on science subjects: Mathematics, Physics, and Chemistry.\n");
      out.write("                Entrance Exams: Admission often requires qualifying entrance exams, which can be:\n");
      out.write("                National-level: (e.g., JEE Main and JEE Advanced in India).\n");
      out.write("                State-level: (e.g., MHT CET in Maharashtra, WBJEE in West Bengal).\n");
      out.write("                University-specific: Some universities have their own exams (e.g., VITEEE for VIT, BITSAT for BITS Pilani).\n");
      out.write("               <br><b> 4. Course Structure and Curriculum</b>\n");
      out.write("                A typical B.Tech curriculum includes the following components:\n");
      out.write("                \n");
      out.write("                <br><b>Year 1: </b>Foundation Courses\n");
      out.write("                Mathematics (Calculus, Linear Algebra)\n");
      out.write("                Physics (Mechanics, Electricity, and Magnetism)\n");
      out.write("                Chemistry (for select branches)\n");
      out.write("                Basic Programming (often C, C++, or Python)\n");
      out.write("                Introduction to Engineering (overview of different branches and disciplines)\n");
      out.write("                Engineering Graphics and Workshop (technical drawing, tools, and machinery basics)\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>Year 2: </b>Core Engineering Courses\n");
      out.write("                Advanced Mathematics (Differential Equations, Statistics)\n");
      out.write("                Core subjects specific to chosen branch (e.g., Circuit Theory for EEE, Thermodynamics for Mechanical)\n");
      out.write("                Engineering Mechanics\n");
      out.write("                Data Structures and Algorithms (for CSE and IT)\n");
      out.write("                Materials Science\n");
      out.write("                Basic Electrical Engineering\n");
      out.write("                Lab Work (e.g., Physics and Chemistry Labs, Electronics Labs)\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>Year 3:</b> Specialized and Advanced Topics\n");
      out.write("                Branch-specific courses: This is where students start focusing on subjects specific to their field.\n");
      out.write("                Mechanical: Fluid Mechanics, Heat Transfer, Machine Design\n");
      out.write("                Civil: Structural Analysis, Hydraulics, Soil Mechanics\n");
      out.write("                CSE: Operating Systems, Database Management Systems, Computer Networks\n");
      out.write("                ECE: Digital Signal Processing, Microprocessors, and Embedded Systems\n");
      out.write("                Electives: Options to study topics like artificial intelligence, machine learning, renewable energy, robotics, etc.\n");
      out.write("                Industry-Oriented Labs and Simulations\n");
      out.write("                Mini Projects: Small-scale projects to apply learned concepts practically.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>Year 4:</b> Advanced and Applied Learning\n");
      out.write("                Capstone Project / Final Year Project: A major project, often in collaboration with an industry partner, where students solve real-world problems in their field.\n");
      out.write("                Internships: Many programs require or encourage internships to gain hands-on experience.\n");
      out.write("                Elective Courses and Special Topics: Students can choose electives to further specialize in areas of interest.\n");
      out.write("                Technical Seminars and Workshops: Additional training on the latest industry trends and tools.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>5. Types of Learning and Evaluation\n");
      out.write("                Lectures and Tutorials:</b> Classroom learning for theoretical concepts.\n");
      out.write("                Laboratories and Workshops: Hands-on experience with equipment, simulations, and software.\n");
      out.write("                Assignments and Projects: Continuous assessments through assignments, mini-projects, and lab reports.\n");
      out.write("                Examinations: Written exams at the end of each semester.\n");
      out.write("                Industrial Visits: Site visits to manufacturing plants, labs, and industries to observe engineering in real-world settings.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>6. Skills Developed\n");
      out.write("                Technical Skills:</b> Proficiency in specific tools, techniques, and software relevant to the chosen branch.\n");
      out.write("                Problem-Solving Skills: Ability to apply engineering principles to solve complex technical issues.\n");
      out.write("                Analytical and Mathematical Skills: Understanding of quantitative methods and data analysis.\n");
      out.write("                Communication and Teamwork: Engineers often work in teams, so communication skills and teamwork are emphasized.\n");
      out.write("                Project Management: Skills in planning, executing, and managing engineering projects.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>7. Career Opportunities After B.Tech\n");
      out.write("                Core Engineering Roles:</b> Design engineer, production engineer, R&D engineer, and quality assurance engineer.\n");
      out.write("                IT and Software Roles: For those with CSE and IT backgrounds, roles like software developer, data analyst, and systems engineer.\n");
      out.write("                Government Jobs: Many B.Tech graduates work in public sector jobs (like Indian Engineering Services in India).\n");
      out.write("                Consulting and Management: Engineers often transition into consulting or management roles after gaining experience.\n");
      out.write("                Higher Studies: Graduates can pursue further education like:\n");
      out.write("                M.Tech (Master of Technology) for deeper specialization.\n");
      out.write("                MS (Master of Science) abroad, especially for research-oriented roles.\n");
      out.write("                MBA (Master of Business Administration) for management positions.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>8. Higher Studies and Certifications</b>\n");
      out.write("                After B.Tech, students can enhance their qualifications with:\n");
      out.write("                M.Tech or ME (Master of Engineering): Specialize further in a chosen field.\n");
      out.write("                Ph.D.: For those interested in research or academia.\n");
      out.write("                Certifications: Courses in programming, data science, machine learning, project management, etc., are popular choices.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>9. Comparison with BE (Bachelor of Engineering)\n");
      out.write("                B.Tech:</b> Often emphasizes application-oriented and practical skills.\n");
      out.write("                BE: Tends to focus more on the theoretical foundations of engineering, though this varies by country and institution.\n");
      out.write("                <br><b>10. Example Semester-Wise Course Outline (Computer Science & Engineering)</b>\n");
